## SLK STACK CONFIGURATION

### 1. Login on ELK Stack
- Go to `https://www.elastic.co/downloads/elasticsearch`
- Select **Free Trial** → Login with your credentials
- Choose **Security Option** → Self-Hosted or Serverless
- Select **SIEM and Security Analysis**
- Cloud Provider: `Amazon Web Services` *(because of the 14-day free trial)*

---

### 2. Installing Agent on Windows Server
- Inside ELK, go to **Integrations** → Set up **Active Directory Entity Analytics**
- Copy the clipboard command and paste it on the Active Directory Server
- When prompted `[y/n]`, select `[y]`
- Terminal message: *"Elastic Agent has been successfully installed."*

![Windows Server Install](https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/windows-server-install.png?raw=true)

- Check on the SIEM; you should see confirmation:

![ELK Agent Setup](https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/ELK-agent-setup.png)

- Select: **Add the Integration**

---

### 3. Collect Identities
- Active Directory Base DN: `activecompany.local`
- Active Directory URL: `LDAP://ActiveCompanyDC.activecompany.local/Default naming context`
- Active Directory User: `administrator`
- Active Directory User Password: `Chosen1#77`
- Dataset: `all`
- Sync Interval: `1h`
- Update Interval: `15m`
- Mark: **Include empty groups**

![Fleet SIEM](https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/fleet-siem.png?raw=true)

- Press **Confirm Data**

---

### 4. Agent Policies
- Navigate inside ELK SIEM → **Assets → Agents → Agent Policies → Create Agent Policy**
- Select: `activecompany`
- Add these three integration policies:
  - Elastic Defend
  - System
  - Windows
- Navigate through Elastic Defend integration → **Integration Policies**
- Click on **Elastic Defend → Edit Integration**
- Set every Policy Setting to **Detect only**

![Policy Settings](https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/policy.png)

---

### 5. Adding Elastic Rules
- Filter by: **Data Source: Active Directory**, **Windows**
- Install all rules
- Select **Tags** → Filter all installed sources
- Select all **1850 Rules**
- Go to **Bulk Actions → Enable**
